fields.descriptive_line: A copy of a 'Catalogue of the Art Treasures of the United Kingdon, collected at Manchester in 1857', with sketches and notes by Doyle, Ellis and Stanley.

fields.name: Art Treasures in Manchester: 150 years on

fields.physical_description: A copy of the 'Catalogue of the Art Treasures of the United Kingdon, collected at Manchester in 1857', interleaved throughout with blank pages on some of which are sketches of certain pictures in the exhibition and studies of groups of visitors etc. by Doyle (after title page, pp. 74, 122, 124, 136 and 154), and the the Hon. Charlotte Isabella Ellis (d.1891) (after pp. 86, 179) and the the Hon. Maude Alethea Stanley (d. 1915), the original owner of the catalogue and with the book plate of Henry herbert Harrod inside the front cover.
